About emoji123.com

Emoji123 in an aggregated list of the most common emojis, emoticons and smileys. You can easily copy and paste your emojis and emoticons directly to Whatsapp, Instagram, Facebook, TikTok and more! in real time.

The following emoji categories are sorted by group. You'll be able to find all current emojis and smileys, as well as use the various emojis on any Apple, Android, and Windows device. Have fun with diving into the colorful world of emojis!

What is an emoji?

An emoji is a graphical image that reflects a certain facial expression. This makes it possible to communicate in a more articulate manner. In word processing systems and web services, emoticons are now automatically converted to emojis. Unicode is translated into a graphic to show emojis. Since 2010, emojis have been available on our cell phones.

What is the meaning of 'emoji'?

Originally meaning pictograph, the word emoji comes from Japanese. Emoji became increasingly popular worldwide in the 2010s after being added to several mobile operating systems. emoji are pictures rather than typographic approximations; the term "emoji" in the strict sense refers to such pictures which can be represented as encoded characters.

Benefits of using emojis

Emojis are universally recognized, and everyone knows what they say. As a result, using these cute creations known as emojis, it's simple to deliver an expression, share a sentiment, grab attention, and even tell a story on social media.

Use emojis in posts and comments

When trying to communicate with your audience, using emojis is a good step. So, when you leave a comment on social media or send a message to your customers, go for it. Emojis will help you communicate with your audience more quickly in these circumstances.

Why I see broken emojis?

When you paste an emoji and it appears broken (an empty box or something similar), it means your Operating System doesn't support it yet.
